<p>I wasn't sure quite how to ask this question-- but I was wondering if there is way to make the pink rectangle in this list float "all the way" to the left so that it appears under the red rectangle. Seems like the pink square wants to float left, but it is being blocked by the height of the rectangle which precedes it. </p>  <p>Looking for a general solutions here-- ran into something similar when I was trying to create my own grid (similar to bootstrap)</p>  <pre><code>[![&lt;div&gt;   &lt;div class='box red'&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;div class='box green'&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;div class='box blue'&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;div class='box pink'&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;/div&gt;  .box {   width: 33.33%;   float: left; }  .red {   background-color: red; } .green {   background-color: green;     height: 100px; } .blue {   background-color: blue;  } .pink {   background-color: pink; } </code></pre>  <p><a href="http://i.stack.imgur.com/nFWny.png" rel="nofollow"><img src="http://i.stack.imgur.com/nFWny.png" alt="enter image description here"></a></p>